comment: Gortat (WAS) sets the screen on Bradley (BOS) and the contact following the screen is marginal.
Bradley (BOS) and Gortat (WAS) briefly engage and separate during rebounding.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor of a 3pt field goal is confirmed.
Smart (BOS) and Gortat (WAS) briefly engage and separate off ball.
Smart (BOS) establishes a legal guarding position outside of the restricted area prior to the contact with Wall (WAS).
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor of a blocking foul is overturned to an offensive foul.
Morris (WAS) makes contact with the ball as Thomas (BOS) attempts the pass.
Gortat (WAS) sets the screen on Bradley (BOS) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Wall (WAS) makes marginal contact with Smart (BOS) that does not affect his FOM off ball.
Wall (WAS) makes incidental contact with Thomas (BOS) that does not affect his SQBR.
Wall (WAS) legally contests Thomas' (BOS) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Thomas (BOS) makes contact with Wall's (WAS) arm that affects his driving shot attempt.
Horford (BOS) establishes a wide screening position and extends his arms into Beal (WAS), delivering the contact.
Gortat (WAS) sets the screen on Thomas (BOS) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Horford (BOS) is in the paint without actively guarding an opponent for longer than three seconds.
Olynyk (BOS) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Beal (WAS) that does not affect his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
Gortat (WAS) makes incidental contact with Horford (BOS) that does not affect his SQBR.
Wall (WAS) legally contests Horford's (BOS) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
[Detectable with stop watch] Porter Jr. (WAS) inbounds the ball within 5 seconds.
Gortat (WAS) sets the screen on Smart (BOS) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Oubre Jr. (WAS) makes contact with Olynyk (BOS) that affects his FOM.

The foul is whistled with approximately 2.7 seconds on the clock, but the clock runs to 1.7 seconds before stopping. The clock should have been stopped earlier automatically on the whistle or by the neutral clock operator. Instant replay is not permitted in this situation.
Horford (BOS) sets the screen on Wall (WAS) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Morris (WAS) legally contests Thomas' (BOS) jump shot attempt.
